name: Mount Washington

trails_config.name: Tuckerman Ravine & Lion Head Loop
trails_config.description: A legendary alpine loop climbing via Tuckerman Ravine and descending Lion Head. Offers the best reward for effort with panoramic summit views and an exciting scramble through a glacial cirque.

trails_config.name: Huntington Ravine Trail
trails_config.description: An expert-only route ascending the steep Huntington Ravine headwall for an adrenaline-pumping climb through boulder fields. Descent via safer trails (Lion Head) is recommended, with epic alpine zone exposure throughout.

generated_description:
The Experience

Standing at 6288 feet, Mount Washington is a standout peak in New Hampshire. Known for its rugged and challenging terrain, it offers a quintessential hiking experience.

The Challenge

Hikers often choose the **Tuckerman Ravine & Lion Head Loop**, a **8.4 mile** route gaining significant elevation. As part of the **NH48 4000-Footers**, it draws peak-baggers from across the region.

Peak Bagging Logic

**Peak Bagging Opportunity:** Consider connecting this hike with **Mount Monroe**, which is just 1.4 miles away. Linking these peaks is a popular way to maximize your day on the trail.
